# Security

> Generated: 2026-03-23T13:40:52.385Z | RepoSage v0.1.0

## Known Security Findings

- No security findings detected in analysis

## Dangerous Patterns to Avoid

- Avoid `eval`, `exec`, shell interpolation with user input
- Validate and sanitize all external inputs
- Never log secrets or credentials
- Use parameterized queries for database access
- Avoid hardcoded secrets; use environment variables

## Security Conventions

- Input validation on all public endpoints
- Output encoding to prevent XSS
- Secure authentication with proper session handling
- Least privilege for file and network access

## For Code Generation

- Never generate code with hardcoded credentials
- Always include input validation on new endpoints
- Use secure defaults for crypto operations
- Sanitize user input before database queries

## For Automations

- Flag security-sensitive changes for manual review
- Check for secrets before committing
- Verify dependency updates for security advisories
- Escalate uncertain security findings

## For Reviews

- Block PRs with obvious security vulnerabilities
- Require security team sign-off for auth changes
- Check for proper error handling (no stack traces to users)
